<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-04-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-04-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="330" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d330">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Baron
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-04-24"><hi rend="italic">April 24,
                                1895</hi>.</date></dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 52.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of February 26 last, stating that the cost of the
                            surveys ordered by the Samoan land commission aggregates perhaps $1,500
                            or $2,000, and asking whether the Government of the United States is
                            willing to pay its pro rata share.</p>
                        <p>In reply I have to inform you that this Government will bear its
                            one-third share of the expenses indicated, and that I have so advised
                            the British ambassador in reply to his recent note upon the subject.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">W. Q. Gresham.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>